article.headline: Joyce Edwards scores 21 points and No. 2 South Carolina cruises past No. 19 Alabama 76-58
article.description: — Joyce Edwards scored 21 points to lead No. 2 South Carolina past No. 19 Alabama 76-58 on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Joyce Edwards scores 21 points and No. 2 South Carolina cruises past No. 19 Alabama 76-58

images.name: Highlight: Edwards paints No. 2 Gamecocks' win over No. 19 Alabama
images.caption: Joyce Edwards scores a career-high 21 points from the paint, including 11 in the fourth quarter, to help South Carolina wash out the Tide, 76-58.

video.description: Joyce Edwards scores a career-high 21 points from the paint, including 11 in the fourth quarter, to help South Carolina wash out the Tide, 76-58.

article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. -- — Joyce Edwards scored 21 points to lead No. 2 South Carolina past No. 19 Alabama 76-58 on Thursday night. Chloe Kitts had 10 points and 13 rebounds, Milay Fulwiley scored 16 points and Te-Hina Paopao added 11 for the Gamecocks (17-1, 5-0 SEC), who have six straight wins over ranked opponents. Zaay Green and Essence Cody each scored 15 points and Aaliyah Nye had 12 for Alabama (16-3, 3-2). Takeaways Alabama: Played without Sarah Ashlee Barker, the Crimson Tide's second-leading scorer who has been sidelined since Jan. 2 with a lower leg injury. South Carolina: Despite shooting just 3 for 20 from 3-point range, the Gamecocks dominated in the paint with 38 points, including 19 second-chance points. Key moment In the first four minutes, South Carolina went on a 12-0 run to set the tone, while Alabama was 0 for 8 during that stretch. Alabama then failed to come closer than four points. Key stat The Gamecocks' reserves have outscored their counterparts by 26.7 points per game this season. South Carolina’s bench outscored Alabama’s 43-2 and outrebounded the Crimson Tide 51-34. Up next South Carolina: Return home Sunday to face No. 13 Oklahoma. Alabama: Travels to face Arkansas on Sunday. ------ Get poll alerts and updates on AP Top 25 basketball throughout the season.
